iCore Platform, V0.1

--INSTALL-- 
A proper java JRE environment should be present. The Platform has been tested with Java 7.
Maven should be installed.

To install the platform, type on a command prompt at the root of the project:

$ mvn install


--ECLIPSE--
To use Eclipse as an IDE, type on a command prompt:

$ mvn eclipse:eclipse

This command should generate the .classpath and .project files.
Then in Eclipse, use the command "File/Import.../Existing project into workspace" and navigate to the location of the .project.

--TEST--

You can run the small demo with the following command:

$ mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="examples.Main"

Press Ctrl-C to exit the demo.
